modules.description: This module provides functions to obtain and manipulate source code position information, such as file name, line number, and character offsets. It works directly with the `position` type, which captures location metadata from the lexer. Concrete use cases include tracking error locations during parsing or generating diagnostic messages with precise source references.

This module provides functions to manipulate and expand source code positions and file paths during preprocessing. It lifts lexing positions into expressions or string literals and resolves relative filenames using a configured directory. Useful for generating accurate source locations in transformed code or handling file path resolution in preprocessors.
